reviews.text: Pizza express chain in Hong Kong is a guarantee of a certain baseline level of Italian food quality. Pizza is thin but good. I always eat well here.
Nice menu and different as well as the same options if you are from the UK!
I ordered chicken wings and they were served cold which means they were made a long time previously, the ginger ale I ordered took 20 mins to recieve, and the pizza tasted like a boxed frozen pizza.

Excellent. Except for the freezing part
 The freezing part needed about 250-300$hk dollars to freeze
not bad but seafood pizza was not what I expected.
